## Python coding standards
- Follow PEP 8. Keep functions small and composable; avoid long procedural scripts when a module/service layer fits better.
- Use type hints for function args + returns (and for public dataclasses/models where helpful).
- Prefer standard library first; add third-party deps only when they materially improve correctness or maintainability.

## Dependencies
- If proposing a new package, explicitly call out:
  - Why it’s needed
  - The exact `requirements.txt` entry to add (pinned version)
  - Any optional extras (e.g. `package[extra]==x.y.z`) only if required
